OL,3,CHospital issues warning after
OL,4,Cnorovirus outbreak on wards
OL,6,F"People who have had diarrhoea,
OL,7,Fvomiting or flu-like symptoms in the
OL,8,Fpast 48 hours are asked to avoid
OL,9,Fvisiting unless it is an emergency or
OL,10,Fthey have been advised to do so by a
OL,11,Fhealthcare professional."
OL,13,FPatients can request to wear PPE which
OL,14,Fcould include face masks, aprons and
OL,15,Fgloves, the hospital has confirmed.
OL,17,FLianne Robinson, Deputy Chief Nurse at
OL,18,FBolton NHS Foundation Trust, urges
OL,19,Fanyone entering the hospital to 'do
OL,20,Feverything you can to help stop the
OL,21,Fspread of norovirus'.
